	<h2>Inspection Procedure</h2>		
	<h4><strong>Inspection Procedure For CTO</strong></h4>
	<ol>
		<li>Facilitator forwards the filled up form of the applicant to the Assistant Engineer/Assistant Executive Engineer for review.</li>
		<li>The Assistant Engineer/ Assistant Executive Engineer reviews the form, clicks on the Inspection tab on the system and selects a particular inspection date after which an email is sent to the applicant wherein the inspection date will be mentioned. It will also be mentioned that on the day of inspection the applicant will have to furnish physical copies of  all the documents mentioned on the checklist that he/she had uploaded earlier .</li>
		<li>The Assistant Engineer/ Assistant Executive Engineer  visits the site on the pre selected date for inspection.</li>
		<li>After he is done with the inspection he needs to submit the inspection report in the desired format (<a href="<?php echo $server_url;?>dept_documents/pcb/FORMAT OF INSPECTION REPORT OF INDUSTRIES.pdf" target="_blank">Format of Inspection Report</a>) and upload the same on the system within 48 hours i.e. two working days(excluding weekends) from the date of inspection.</li>
	</ol>
	<h2>Inspection Guidelines</h2>		
	
	<ol>
		<li>The Assistant Engineer/ Assistant Executive Engineer should visit the site on pre selected date.</li>
		<li>He should submit the inspection report in the desired format (<a href="<?php echo $server_url;?>dept_documents/pcb/FORMAT OF INSPECTION REPORT OF INDUSTRIES.pdf" target="_blank">Format of Inspection Report</a>) within 48 hours i.e. two workings days(excluding weekends) from the date of inspection.</li>
		<li>The applicant should keeps the physical copies of all the documents ready on the date of inspection.</li>
		<li>The  Assistant Engineer/ Assistant Executive Engineer should click on the inspection tab on the system and select  a particular date</li>
	</ol>
	</p>
